article.headline: East Tenn. St. 99, North Florida 83
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Tim Smith scored a team-high 26 points to lead East Tennessee State to a 99-83 win Sunday over North Florida in an Atlantic Sun Conference game. Smith hit 10 of 19 shots, all from inside the arc, for the Buccaneers (14-8, 11-4). Dillion Sneed, Ben Rhoda and Smith all reached double figures by halftime, giving East Tennessee a 57-35 lead at the break. Rhoda finished with 22 points, and Sneed finished with 15. Rashad Williams led the Ospreys (6-16, 3-12) with a career-high 32 points, besting his previous season high by seven. Williams also had 12 rebounds for the double-double. Alain Laroche scored 21 points for North Florida, including 15 in the second half. After falling behind by 17 in the first 9 minutes, the Ospreys cut the deficit to 10 three times but could never get closer. North Florida never came closer than 14 points in the second half. The Buccaneers have won 13 of their last 15 games, including 11 in conference play. The win moved East Tennessee into second place in the Atlantic Sun Conference.
